# Agent Plugin Architecture

Read [AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md) for full guide. Summary:

## Core (contracts only — no implementations)

- `agent/` — agent loop
- `types/` — neutral shared types
- `llm/provider.go` — Provider interface + provider registry
- `tools/tool.go` — Tool interface + Registry
- `config/` — configuration
- `plugin/` — Plugin interfaces + Bootstrap

## Plugins (all implementations)

- `plugins/tools/*` — tools
- `plugins/providers/*` — LLM providers
- `plugins/prompt/*` — system prompts
- `plugins/runner/*` — REPL / runners
- Register in `plugins/builtin/builtin.go` only

## Before adding code

1. Contract or implementation?
2. Implementation → `plugins/`, then register in `builtin.Default`
3. Never add tool/provider/prompt implementations to `agent/`, `llm/` (except types), or `tools/` (except interface)
4. Avoid import cycles: `plugin` uses `AgentHandle` interface, not `*agent.Agent`

## Adding a tool (minimal)

Create `plugins/tools/foo/foo.go` with `Tool` + `Plugin`, append `foo.Plugin{}` to `builtin.Default`.
